                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/8924.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Private information not confirmed indicates Mexican Government gathering
                    information for the purpose of compelling foreign corporations as well as native
                    corporations to make forced loans to Mexican Government in the form of purchase
                    of bonds to relieve Government’s financial condition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
